					<div id="post_message_1774814">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Not sure if this is considered big news, but Brad McQuaid left Sigil Games yesterday to return to the Everquest team. He states: <div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				In fact, some of my first work as a game designer on the team will be working on areas that have been alluded to since launch. I can’t say more than that, of course, but I’m sure you can imagine how exciting this is for me.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>  Neither of the links below give more info, I'm guessing they wanted him back to work on EQ Next.<br />
<br />
Links:<a href="http://www.polygon.com/2013/3/11/4091372/everquest-brad-mcquaid-returns" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.polygon.com/2013/3/11/409...cquaid-returns</a><br />
<a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/eq/index.php?threads/12-years-i-feel-so-old.4319/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://forums.station.sony.com/eq/in...l-so-old.4319/</a>
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
