			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Aradune comes home
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1774969">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							EQ was fun despite McQuaid.  EQ was great because previous to that, the MMO trend was being controlled by Ultima, which wanted more of a &quot;fun place to play around&quot; while EQ wanted a grueling, endless treadmill.  The EQ grind-style was okay, but WoW perfected it as a game.  That's why no one can operate a game using the same style, because once you've done the daily Grinding for several years, you never have the patience to do it again.<br />
<br />
While the Lore in EQ seemed deep, it was like the Lore in Elder Scrolls games: Meaningless for playing the game.  For the Lore to really be deep and meaningful, understanding the Lore should add to the game.  Understanding the Lore should give you an advantage, not just be &quot;Oh, cool, I understand Quarm now&quot;
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
