		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Aradune comes home
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1776598">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Shatter</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1776058#post1776058" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">I remember dying on a raid in POF, 6 hour corpse recovery lol</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Six hours? Fucking lightweight! :P  Try our rolling 3 DAY cr in fear soon after Kunark launched, back when people still thought running to the southeast corner and trying to camp a cleric out was a clever idea!  Lots of login info was shared that weekend I can tell ya, including mine! Tagad had his work cut out for him.<br />
<br />
Or the 20-some hour CR in Roots back on the Toril/Sojourn MUD (Where Aradone played before he left to go design EQ), where corpses decay after 2 hours leaving a pile of gear on the ground in a game where gear on the ground does not survive a game reboot in a game that rebooted about once a day....  Talk about stress.<br />
  There was also a zone called Crypts I think that needed a key to get in, and if you went in with the key and wiped (which wasnt so hard to do, especially early on) then it was impossible to get back iin and recover your corpses, and you had to pray that the game crashed/rebooted before your corpses decayed in 2 hours or you lost everything. (A crash/reboot reset the 2 hour corpse timer, but more importantly reset the key location so you could get it again). I got a desperate message for help from someone in a late-night group that got careless and took the key in with them and wiped, asking if there was any way I could think of to rescue them.  I told them there was no way to get back in, but dont panic yet, there's something I can try if you give me 20 minutes. That was the one time I ever intentionally used a crash bug in my 5 years in that game, but it saved them which gave me some nice warm fuzzies.  They were very lucky too- Only myself and my regular partner in that MUD, Mplor (who anyone who played EQ on Veeshan might remember from there also) knew of that crash bug, or could get to it since at the time everyone else was terrified of the zone it was in and had never explored it due to newbie trauma in it, and Mplor wasnt on. So it was double warm-fuzzies for me, really.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" />
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
